main event: A sighting on March 3, 1956, of a white fluorescent-like light near Andrews AFB.
interesting points: The object was observed for approximately 30 seconds., The shape of the object was not discernible and appeared as a pen held at arm's length., The light intensity faded and increased at regular intervals without blinking., The object was observed to be climbing and turning right., Estimated speed of the object was 700 knots.
witness description: No report of witnesses in the file.
